s diverse viewpoints. This approach significantly advances the state-of-the-art by unifying three critical components: (1) implicit canonicalization via cycle consistency, (2) pose-invariant representation learning without explicit pose supervision, and (3) geometric enhancement through geodesic-aware latent spaces. Potential impact includes broader applicability in robotics, AR/VR, and autonomous systems where reliable 3D understanding from monocular inputs is essential.",
